<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Kerala Special Meal</title>
	<link href="~/css/kerala.css" rel="stylesheet" />
</head>
<body>

    <header>
        <h1>Kerala Special Meal</h1>
    </header>

    <section class="recipe-container">
       

        <div class="description">
            <p>A traditional Kerala meal, also known as **Sadhya**, consists of a variety of dishes served on a banana leaf. It includes rice, curries, pickles, papadam, and payasam, making it a delightful feast!</p>
        </div>

        <div class="ingredients">
            <h2>Items in Kerala Special Meal</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Boiled Rice</li>
                <li>Sambar</li>
                <li>Avial (Mixed Vegetable Curry with Coconut)</li>
                <li>Thoran (Stir-fried Vegetables with Coconut)</li>
                <li>Olan (Pumpkin & Coconut Milk Curry)</li>
                <li>Pachadi (Yogurt-Based Dish)</li>
                <li>Kootu Curry (Chickpea & Coconut Curry)</li>
                <li>Pulissery (Buttermilk Curry)</li>
                <li>Pickles (Mango/Lemon)</li>
                <li>Papadam (Crispy Lentil Wafers)</li>
                <li>Banana Chips</li>
                <li>Payasam (Traditional Dessert)</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="instructions">
            <h2>How to Serve</h2>
            <ol>
                <li>Traditionally, Kerala Sadhya is served on a banana leaf.</li>
                <li>Each dish is arranged in a specific order, starting with rice in the center.</li>
                <li>First, have a small serving of salt, pickle, and papadam.</li>
                <li>Serve sambar over rice, followed by other curries.</li>
                <li>End the meal with a sweet payasam.</li>
                <li>Enjoy the authentic Kerala flavors with hands for the best experience!</li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    </section>

</body>
</html>
